Title: Expands the definition of veteran to include members of the United States public health service
Summary: Expands the definition of veteran to include members of the United States public health service to provide such members with access to the same benefits as members of the United States armed forces.
LawCode: Amd §§350, 364, 369-b & 369-h, Exec L; amd §210, Ec Dev L; amd §63, Pub Off L; amd §§458, 458-a & 458-b, RPT L
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the executive law, the economic development law, the public officers law and the real property tax law, in relation to expanding the definition of veteran to include members of the United States public health service
